https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/5IpBIvWvCwfDUaaWKAocc8pXoWq.jpg A cinematic version of the Royal Winnipeg Ballet's adaptation of Bram Stoker's gothic novel Dracula. Filmed in a style reminiscent of silent Expressionist cinema of the early 20th century (complete with intertitles and monochrome photography), it uses dance to tell the story of a sinister but intriguing immigrant who preys upon young English women. Dracula: Pages from a Virgin's Diary
